<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FF78FD3EFDD0FB05" blockId="541.[136,778,173,2070]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FEF6FD21FE6CFCCB" box="[307,425,751,778]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 361E</figureCitation>
) distinct, slightly longerthan wide (84×72 μm), tapering to narrow apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FF55FCFDFF3BFC8F" box="[144,254,819,846]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 361F</figureCitation>
) archedposteriorly, 117 μmlong, 6-segmented; third and fourth segments articulated from each other only on one surface; first segment with 2 setae; setation of other segments obscure due to similarity with setules; third, fifth and terminal segments each bearing 1 small aesthetasc. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FE4FFC13FDCCFC39" box="[394,521,989,1016]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 361G</figureCitation>
) stout, 4-segmented; coxa, basis, and first endopodal segment unarmed; basis shorter than first endopodal segment; narrower second endopodal segment about 2.3 times longer than wide (41×18 μm) and as long as first segment: armed with 3 small setae plus small terminal claw, about one-third as long as second endopodal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FF78FB05FE77F8C7" blockId="541.[136,778,173,2070]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FEEBFB05FE6CFB27" box="[302,425,1227,1254]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 361H</figureCitation>
) simple, unornamented, with short,broadposteromedian lobe.Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FDA2FB23FD09FAC9" box="[615,716,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig.361I</figureCitation>
) with coxal gnathobase bearing 4 teeth on distal half of medial margin and pectinate proximal half of medial margin: palp consisting of basis and 2-segmented endopod; basis with 1 seta mediodistally; exopod completely fused with basis, represented by outer lobe of basis and pair of large setae at base of lobe; endopod 2-segmented, incompletely articulated from basis, with 1 broad seta on first segment and 4 setaeon second. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FDCDFA33FDB9F9D9" box="[520,636,1533,1560]" captionStart="FIGURE 362" captionStartId="543.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[144,1414,230,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-194@543.[136,1451,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="543" captionText="FIGURE 362. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxillule; B, maxilla; C, maxilliped; D, leg 1; E, leg 2; F, leg 3; G, leg 4. Scale bars: A–C, 0.01 mm; D–G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592038" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592038/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 362A</figureCitation>
) armedwith 6 setae on arthrite, 1 on coxal epipodite, 1 on basis, 4 on exopod and 3 on endopod; coxal endite absent. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FF55F9ADFECEF9BF" box="[144,267,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 362" captionStartId="543.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[144,1414,230,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-194@543.[136,1451,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="543" captionText="FIGURE 362. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxillule; B, maxilla; C, maxilliped; D, leg 1; E, leg 2; F, leg 3; G, leg 4. Scale bars: A–C, 0.01 mm; D–G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592038" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592038/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 362B</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; syncoxa bearing 2 endites, with 3 setae on first endite and 2 on second; basis with strong claw plus 1 seta; small endopod with 1 seta on first segment and 3 setaeon second. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FDB6F907FD21F925" box="[627,740,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 362" captionStartId="543.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[144,1414,230,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-194@543.[136,1451,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="543" captionText="FIGURE 362. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxillule; B, maxilla; C, maxilliped; D, leg 1; E, leg 2; F, leg 3; G, leg 4. Scale bars: A–C, 0.01 mm; D–G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592038" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592038/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 362C</figureCitation>
) as small lobe bearing 4 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FF78F8C0FB54FECA" blockId="541.[136,778,173,2070]" lastBlockId="541.[810,1451,173,267]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FEF6F8C3FE57F8E9" box="[307,402,1805,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 362" captionStartId="543.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[144,1414,230,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-194@543.[136,1451,197,1433]" captionTargetPageId="543" captionText="FIGURE 362. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxillule; B, maxilla; C, maxilliped; D, leg 1; E, leg 2; F, leg 3; G, leg 4. Scale bars: A–C, 0.01 mm; D–G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592038" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592038/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 362</figureCitation>
D-G) biramous with 3-segmented exopods; endopods 3-segmented inlegs 1–3, but 2- segmented in leg 4. Protopod 2-segmented in leg 1, but unsegmented in legs 2–4. Inner coxal seta absent in legs 1–4. Leg 1 lacking innerdistal element on basis. Outer seta on basis present only in leg 3. Endopod of leg 1 strongly curved inwards. First exopodal segment of legs 3 and 4 and second exopodal segment of legs 2 and 4 each bearing spiniform outer distal process. Outer setae on third exopodal segment of legs 2–4 vestigial. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FC9AFDCCFAE4FD9E" blockId="541.[810,1451,513,778]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED4C3828FC7CFDCFFBF5FDDD" box="[953,1072,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 361" captionStartId="542.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1354,205,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-21@542.[191,1397,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="542" captionText="FIGURE 361. Ammonixys quadridens gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, ventrolateral; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, anterior part of prosome, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.2 mm; C, D, 0.05 mm; E–I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592036/files/figure.png" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Fig. 361C</figureCitation>
) consisting of outer lobe tipped with 1 small seta and inner, tapering, sclerotized process; left and right inner processes interconnected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FC9AFDA9FBE5FD40" blockId="541.[810,1451,513,778]" box="[863,1056,615,642]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FC9AFDA9FC59FD40" bold="true" box="[863,924,615,641]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4C3828FC9AFD47FA6FFCC8" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4C3828FC9AFD47FA6FFCC8" blockId="541.[810,1451,513,778]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FC9AFD47FC09FD62" bold="true" box="[863,972,649,675]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Remarks</emphasis>
.Itisnoteworthythat 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FB6FFD47FA6EFD62" box="[1194,1451,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Ammonixysquadridens</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FCEFFD65FC1DFD04" bold="true" box="[810,984,683,709]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4C3828FCEFFD65FC1DFD04" box="[810,984,683,709]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was extracted along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4C3828FB38FD62FA6EFD04" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1277,1451,683,709]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FB38FD62FA6EFD04" box="[1277,1451,683,709]" italics="true" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Doroixys obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4C3828FCEFFD03FC42FD29" box="[810,903,717,744]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FCEFFD03FC45FD26" bold="true" box="[810,896,717,743]" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and two other species of copepods (
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4C3828FAEAFD03FA6EFD26" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[1327,1451,717,743]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FAEAFD03FA6EFD26" box="[1327,1451,717,743]" italics="true" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Scolecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4C3828FC45FD21FBCCFCC8" box="[896,1033,751,777]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Ascidicolidae" genus="Haplostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="541" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4C3828FC45FD21FBCCFCC8" box="[896,1033,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="541" pageNumber="542">Haplostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.), all from the same ascidian host.
</paragraph>
